    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Commissioned military officers ranking above brigadier generals and below lieutenant generals. Major generals command military units called divisions, which are made up of 7,000-22,000 troops, and their insignia are two stars.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
